ip News |date=18 October 1862 |page_number=11 |issue=24380 |column=F }}</ref><ref name=S301062/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Ramonita'' \n|flag=[[File:Gdansk flag.svg|22px]] [[Danzig]] \n|desc=The [[brig]] ran aground on Smith's Knoll, in the North Sea off the coast of [[Norfolk]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]]. She was on a voyage from [[Alloa]], [[Clackmannanshire]], United Kingdom to [[New York City|New York]], United States. She was refloated and taken in to [[Great Yarmouth]], Norfolk in a leaky condition.<ref name=S181062/><ref name=AL1862>{{cite journal |url=https://research.mysticseaport.org/item/l0237571862/353/ |title=Brigs |journal=American Lloyd's Register of American and Foreign Shipping 1862 |year=1862 |publisher=American Lloyds |location=New York}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Stonewall''\n|flag={{flag|Confederate States|1861}}\n|desc=American Civil War, Union blockade: The [[schooner]] was burned at Taylor's Bayou by boat crews from the [[gunboat]] {{USS|Rachel Seaman|1861|6}} and the armed [[Steamship|steamer]] {{USS|Kensington|1862|6}} (both {{navy|United States|1861}}).<ref name=usnlpcivilwarchronologyJulDec1862/><ref name=gainesp172>Gaines, p. 172.</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Yarmouth''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was wrecked near \"Warberg\", Sweden. Her crew were rescued. She was on a voyage from [[Sunderland, County Durham]] to [[Stettin]].<ref name=Times171062/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==16 October==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=16 October 1862 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Europa'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship ran aground on the Gunfleet Sand, in the [[North Sea]] off the coast of [[Essex]].<ref name=LM171062/> She was on a voyage from [[Archangelsk]], Russia to London.<ref name=S221062a/> She was refloated on 20 October and towed in to [[Harwich]], Essex.<ref name=S231062/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship='