 unknown\n|desc=The [[schooner]] was lost near [[Port Angeles, Washington|Port Angeles]], [[Washington Territory]].<ref name=gainesp194>Gaines, p. 194.</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Cincinnatus'' \n|flag={{flag|United States|1861}}\n|desc=The [[full-rigged ship]] was destroyed by fire in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] before 3 October. She was on a voyage from [[Newport, Monmouthshire]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]] to [[Shanghai]], [[Qing dynasty|China]].<ref name=S061062/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Comet'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=American Civil War: The [[schooner]] was destroyed by {{USS|Dacotah}} ({{navy|United States|1861}}). She was on a voyage from [[Matanzas]] to [[Havana]], Cuba.<ref name=S011162>{{Cite news |title=Mercantile Ship News |newspaper=The Standard |location=London |date=1 November 1862 |issue=11926 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Commerce''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The[[collier (ship type)|collier]], a [[brig]], foundered in the North Sea {{convert|30|nmi|km}} off [[Spurn Point]], [[East Riding of Yorkshire|Yorkshire]]. Her crew were rescued by a fishing [[lugger]].<ref name=Times281062>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Collier Vessels, Shields, Oct. 26 |date=28 October 1862 |page_number=9 |issue=24388 |column=D }}</ref><ref name=NC311062/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Conchita''\n|flag={{flag|Confederate States of America|1861}}\n|desc=American Civil War, [[Union blockade]]: The [[schooner]] was captured and burned off the coast of [[Louisiana]] or [[Texas]] near [[Calcasieu Pass]] and [[Sabine Pass]].<ref>Gaines, pp. 167-168.</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Cybele'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was wrecked near \"Marberg\". She was on a voyage from [[Riga]], Russia to a Dutch port.<ref name=LM211062b/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Corsair''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship fou