 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Trekboer Cobern'' \n|flag={{flagicon|UKGBI}} [[British Cape Colony|Cape Colony]]\n|desc=The ship was driven ashore and wrecked in Algoa Bay with the loss of a crew member.<ref name=MC071144/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Trois Enfans'' \n|flag={{flag|France}}\n|desc=The ship was wrecked on the Sherweather Sands, in the [[Bristol Channel]]. She was on a voyage from Newport to [[Brest, France|Brest]], [[Finist\u00e8re]].<ref name=MC260844/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Union'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was driven ashore on [[Eierland]], [[North Holland]], Netherlands. She was on a voyage from [[Stettin]] to [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]], [[East Riding of Yorkshire|Yorkshire]]. She was refloated ad taken in to a port on [[Texel]], North Holland.<ref name=Times300844/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Vrow Antina'' \n|flag={{flag|Hamburg|admiralty}}\n|desc=The ship was wrecked on the Movinsand. Her crew were rescued. She was on a voyage from a Scottish port to Hamburg.<ref name=MC260844/><ref name=GH020944/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''574'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship ran aground at [[Gloucester]]. She was on a voyage from Gloucester to [[Quebec City]] [[Province of Canada]], [[British North America]]. She was refloated the next day and taken in to Gloucester.<ref name=CM260844/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==22 August==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=22 August 1844 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''\u00c6olus'' \n|flag={{flagicon|UKGBI}} [[Van Diemen's Land]]\n|desc=The [[sloop]] was wrecked opposite the coast of [[Huon Island]].<ref name=LE040944>{{Cite news |url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/newspaper/article/36237747 |title=(From the Hobart Town Advertiser) |newspaper=Launceston Examiner |location=Launceston, Van Diemen's Land |date=4 September 1844 |page=7 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Glasgow'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}