astle upon Tyne]], [[Northumberland]] to [[Hooksiel]], [[Kingdom of Hanover]].<ref name=Times300844/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Forth'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship ran aground and was damaged at [[Plymouth]], [[Devon]]. She was refloated the next day.<ref name=CM260844/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Jane and Helen'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[smack (ship)|smack]] was driven ashore and wrecked at [[Porthdinllaen]], Caernarfonshire. She was on a voyage from [[Caernarfon|Caernarvon]] to [[Southampton]], [[Hampshire]].<ref name=MC220844>{{Cite news |title=Shipping Intelligence |newspaper=The Morning Chronicle |location=London |date=14 August 1844 |issue=23343 }}</ref><ref name=CM260844/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==19 August==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=19 August 1844 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Amity'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship ran aground off [[Ameland]], [[Friesland]], Netherlands. She was on a voyage from [[Liverpool]], [[Lancashire]] to [[Hamburg]].<ref name=CM290844/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Devotion'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was driven ashore and wrecked at [[Merlimont]], [[Pas-de-Calais]], France. She was on a voyage from [[Newport, Monmouthshire]] to [[Altona, Hamburg|Altona]].<ref name=MP230844>{{Cite news |title=Ship News |newspaper=The Morning Post |location=London |date=23 August 1844 |issue=22967 }}</ref><ref name=CM260844/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Fortuna'' \n|flag={{flag|Norway|1844}}\n|desc=The ship was abandoned in the [[North Sea]] ({{coord|54|36|N|4|29|E}}). Four of her nine crew were rescued by ''Hudson'' ({{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}), the rest were left on board. ''Fortuna'' was on a voyage from [[Narva]], [[Russian Empire|Russia]] to [[Amsterdam]], [[North Holland]], Netherlands.<ref name=Times100944/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Hoffnung'' \n|flag={{flag|Hamburg|admiralty}}\n|des