ed her voyage. She arrived at [[Gravesend, Kent]], United Kingdom on 28 August.<ref name=MP290844>{{Cite news |title=Ship News |newspaper=The Morning Post |location=London |date=29 August 1844 |issue=22972 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Gerbrand'' \n|flag={{flag|Hamburg|admiralty}}\n|desc=The ship was driven ashore and wrecked on [[Ameland]], [[Friesland]], Netherlands with the loss of all but one of her crew. She was on a voyage from Hamburg to [[Rouen]], [[Seine-Inf\u00e9rieure]], France.<ref name=GH300844/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Jane and Eliza'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was driven ashore at [[Petten]], South Holland. She was on a voyage from [[Newport, Monmouthshire]] to [[Dordrecht]], South Holland.<ref name=CM260844/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Methesis'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[barque]] ran aground on the Elbow End Bank, at the mouth of the [[River Tay]] and was severely damaged. She was on a voyage from [[Ichaboe Island]], [[Portuguese West Africa]] to [[Aberdeen]]. She was refloated and towed in to [[Ferry-Port on Craig]], [[Fife]].<ref name=CM260844>{{Cite news |title=Shipping Intelligence |newspaper=Caledonian Mercury |location=Edinburgh |date=26 August 1844 |issue=19392 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Thomas Perkins'' \n|flag={{flag|United States|1847}}\n|desc=The ship was driven ashore at [[New York City|New York]]. She was later refloated.<ref name=Times180944/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==21 August==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=21 August 1844 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Ann and Mary'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[brig]] foundered in the [[Irish Sea]] west of the [[Isle of Man]] with the loss of all hands.<ref name=MP270944>{{Cite news |title=Ship News |newspaper=The Morning Post |location=London |date=27 September 1844 |issue=22997 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Emma Maria'' \n|flag={{flag|France}}\